info.title: Frontend API Specification
info.description: This is an API specification that allows GET Cloud FrontEnd 2.0 to request for data to GET Cloud BackEnd 2.0.

values is an array of array, each of which represents one row of the history log. The number of values elements in basic, advanced, and other must match. The number of elements in each array in values must match the number of elements in fields. See the example below.

y is an array of array, each of which represents each y_names (not x!). The number of elements in each array in y must match the number of elements in x. See the example below.

Get the instant logs'
  1. x values (x)
  2. possible series names for dropdown left/right axis menu (y_names), and
  3. y values for each y_names (y))
of a given MUI on the requested date range.

y is an array of array, each of which represents each y_names (not x!). The number of elements in each array in y must match the number of elements in x. See the example below.

Get the list of left/right axis dropdown menu for history chart tab.
  • The number of elements in yaxis1 and yaxis2 must match. But the number of elements on each yaxis2 doesn't have to equal the number of elements of yaxis1 - 1.
  • When none from both left and right axis dropdown is chosen, both dropdown menus should contain values from yaxis1.
  • When nothing from the right axis is chosen but yaxis1[1] (Charge active time) from the left axis dropdown is chosen, then the right axis should change to contain the list from yaxis2[1] (["Charge duration", "Charge resting time", "Charged Ah"])
  • When nothing from the left axis is chosen but yaxis1[2] (Charge resting time) from the right axis dropdown is chosen, then the left axis should change to contain the list from yaxis2[2] (["Charge duration", "Charge active time", "Charged Ah"])

parameters.name: id
parameters.description: Fleet id or fleetgroup id that the user wants to add its tab or configure its properties.

200.description: Get the list of enabled tabs (alarms, soc, equalizing, charging) and its monitoring properties (equalizingCycles, chargingPerWeek) of the given fleet Id/fleetgroup Id.

Get the daily status regarding alarms (=days with alarms) of a given fleet/fleetgroup on the requested month. 0 = no alarm that day (green), 1 = less severe alarms that day (orange), 2 = severe alarms that day (red), -1 = the day is not finished (blue)

Get the list of alarms of a given fleet Id or fleetgroup Id on the requested month. The number of elements for alarmNames and quantity must match. Values in quantity must be > 0 (null and 0 are not allowed).

Get the alarm logs of all devices on a given fleet Id/fleetgroup Id on the requested month. data must contain fields and values.

values is an array of array, each of which represents one row of the alarm log. The number of elements in each array in values must match the number of elements in fields. See the example below.

Get the daily status of the fleet/fleetgroup, whether all charging is completed or not, on a given fleet/fleetgroup, on the requested month. 0 = all BMUs+BMSs have been charged (green), 1 = some BMUs/BMSs have NOT been charged (orange), 2 = many BMUs/BMSs have NOT been charged, -1 = the day is not finished (blue)
Get how many % Batteries charged in this fleet/fleetgroup on the requested month. The first element of data is always day 1 of the requested month. Values in data are 0-100 or null.

Get the charging logs of all chargers on a given fleet Id/fleetgroup Id on the requested month. data must contain fields and values.

values is an array of array, each of which represents one row of the charging log. The number of elements in each array in values must match the number of elements in fields. See the example below.

Get the number of missed charging for each batteries on a fleet Id / fleetgroup Id on the requested month. data must contain fields and values.

values is an array of array, each of which represents one row on the table. The number of elements in each array in values must match the number of elements in fields. The number of elements in values equals to the number of batteries under that fleet/fleetgroup. See the example below.

Get the daily status regarding deep discharged batteries (daily deep discharges) under a given fleet/fleetgroup on the requested month. 0 = all batteries never experience deep discharges that day (green), 1 = some batteries experience deep discharges (orange), 2 = many batteries experience deep discharges, -1 = the day is not finished (blue)
Get how many % Batteries are deep discharged on the requested month. The first element of data is always day 1 of the requested month. Values in data are 0-100 or null.

Get the number of deep charges per battery on a fleet Id / fleetgroup Id on the requested month. data must contain fields and values.

values is an array of array, each of which represents one row on the table. The number of elements in each array in values must match the number of elements in fields. The number of elements in values equals to the number of batteries under that fleet/fleetgroup. See the example below.

Get the SOC logs of all devices on a given fleet Id/fleetgroup Id on the requested month. data must contain fields and values.

values is an array of array, each of which represents one row in the table. The number of elements in each array in values must match the number of elements in fields. See the example below.
Get how many % of all Batteries on a given fleet Id/fleetgroup Id that has completed equalization on the requested year.

Get the number of missed equalization for each batteries on a fleet Id / fleetgroup Id on the requested month. data must contain fields and values.

values is an array of array, each of which represents one row on the table. The number of elements in each array in values must match the number of elements in fields. The number of elements in values equals to the number of batteries under that fleet/fleetgroup. See the example below.
Get the equalizing logs of all devices on a given fleet on the requested month.
